summary: An ordinance accepting deeds from Emily McCullagh, spinster; W.C. Sutton, a widower; Dorothy Boniface and Peter Q. Boniface, her husband; Edward Ellwanger and Inga N. Ellwanger, his wife; Anges McCullagh, a widow; Helen Rector, a widow; A.E. Priem and Mae Miller Priem, husband and wife; Geo. F. Rohrig and Bertha Rohrig, his wife; to the City of Seattle, for street purposes and laying off Kenyon Place Southwest.
